      "content": "No, you should never double the dose of ibuprofen or give extra-strength formulations to a child, as this can cause severe stomach bleeding, kidney failure, or even death. Instead, give him a single standard dose of ibuprofen and a dose of acetaminophen about 30 minutes apart if he is still uncomfortable, but do not exceed the recommended maximum daily limit for his age and weight. If he is crying uncontrollably or has a fever above 39°C, you should call your pediatrician immediately for professional guidance.",
